{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sorted","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> [","kind":"text"},{"text":"Element","preciseIdentifier":"s:ST7ElementQa","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Sequence/Element"},{"text":"]","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"return-value","type":"heading","text":"Return Value"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A sorted array of the sequence’s elements."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can sort any sequence of elements that conform to the "},{"code":"Comparable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"protocol by calling this method. Elements are sorted in ascending order."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here’s an example of sorting a list of students’ names. Strings in Swift"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conform to the "},{"code":"Comparable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol, so the names are sorted in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ascending order according to the less-than operator ("},{"code":"<","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"code":["let students: Set = [\"Kofi\", \"Abena\", \"Peter\", \"Kweku\", \"Akosua\"]","let sortedStudents = students.sorted()","print(sortedStudents)","// Prints \"[\"Abena\", \"Akosua\", \"Kofi\", \"Kweku\", \"Peter\"]\""],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To sort the elements of your sequence in descending order, pass the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"greater-than operator (","type":"text"},{"code":">","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") to the ","type":"text"},{"code":"sorted(by:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let descendingStudents = students.sorted(by: >)","print(descendingStudents)","// Prints \"[\"Peter\", \"Kweku\", \"Kofi\", \"Akosua\", \"Abena\"]\""],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The sorting algorithm is guaranteed to be stable. A stable sort"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"preserves the relative order of elements that compare as equal."}]},{"name":"Complexity","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"O("},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" log "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"), where "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is the length of the sequence."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/DefaultIndices"]]},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["/documentation/swift/defaultindices/sorted()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/DefaultIndices/sorted()"},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","conformance":{"availabilityPrefix":[{"text":"Available when","type":"text"}],"constraints":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Element"},{"text":" conforms to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Comparable"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"conformancePrefix":[{"text":"Conforms when","type":"text"}]},"title":"sorted()","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"externalID":"s:STsSL7ElementRpzrlE6sortedSayABGyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:SI","extendedModule":"Swift","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"ki